                        <h2 class="title">Introduction</h2>
                        <div class="entry">
                            <p> I am a fourth year PhD student at Leiden Observatory, Leiden University in the Netherlands. My PhD is also partly funded by ASTRON, so spend some of my time up in Dwingeloo.
                            <br />
                            My research interests cover a wide range of Extragalactic Astronomy, from Large Scale Structure down to the evolution of galaxies. See the Research tab for info on my previous and current research as well as my interests.
                            </p>  
                        </div>
                        <h2 class="title">About Me</h2>
                        <div class="entry">
                            <p> I was born and grew up near Johannesburg, South Africa, but lived in Cape Town for six years. I did my BSc in Physics and Astrophysics at the University of Cape Town, continuing with my Honours as part of the National Astrophysics and Space Science Programme, and then onto my MSc in the <a href="www.strw.leidenuniv.nl">Department of Astronomy</a>, University of Cape Town, South Africa. 
                            <br />
                            My love of all things astronomical stems from an early age, although my particular research interests now lie outside our own galaxy. I enjoy teaching and have tutored a number of Astronomy and Mathematics courses at UCT during my time there. I also enjoy doing public outreach and have volunteered at the Open Nights held at the South African Astronomical Observatory. 
                            <br />
                            </p>  
